  "prompt": "How hard is it to get into KTH Royal Institute of Technology for a bachelor's degree?",
  "response": "Getting into KTH Royal Institute of Technology for a bachelor's degree can be competitive. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Admission Requirements:\n- Strong academic background, particularly in mathematics and science\n- High school diploma or equivalent\n- Proof of English proficiency (IELTS or TOEFL)\n- Specific course prerequisites for different programs\n\n2. Selectivity:\n- KTH is a prestigious university in Sweden\n- Admission is competitive, especially for international students\n- Acceptance rates vary by program but are generally around 20-30%\n\n3. Application Process:\n- Must apply through the Swedish national application system\n- Meet both university and program-specific requirements\n- Submit complete application with all necessary documents\n- Early application is recommended\n\n4. Factors Affecting Admission:\n- Academic grades\n- Standardized test scores\n- Relevant extracurricular activities\n- Personal statement\n- Specific program requirements\n\n5. International Student Considerations:\n- International applicants may face additional requirements\n- Limited number of spots for international students\n- Competitive scholarship opportunities\n\nWhile admission is challenging, well-prepared students with strong academic backgrounds have a good chance of being accepted.",
